You must not include anything other than the number on this final line, and the answer must directly respond to the specific question in the problem (e.g., cost of 1 kg of apples, total money saved, etc.).

If any ambiguity exists (e.g., interpretation of "two times cheaper"), resolve it in accordance with standard math vocabulary: "n times cheaper" means "1/n" the cost.

Always use the following format for your output:

Step 1: [Explicit description of the first action with working/calculation]

Step 2: [Next explicit statement, calculation or check]

...

#### <final numeric answer>

Important: Never skip steps, never omit calculations, never introduce extra text before or after the numeric answer. Follow this method rigorously for all question types including purchases, group calculations, and "how much is saved/left/more" type questions.
